---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const pageTitle = "Why Is Iceland the Best Place to Experience the 2026 Solar Eclipse?";
---
<BaseLayout title={pageTitle}>
  <!-- JSON-LD (from your original file) -->
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why Is Iceland the Best Place to Experience the 2026 Solar Eclipse?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Iceland's proximity to the path of totality, minimal light pollution, and wide open landscapes make it an ideal spot to view the 2026 eclipse." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What Is Happening on 12 August 2026?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A total solar eclipse will pass over parts of the Arctic and North Atlantic, including Northern Iceland. The Moon will completely cover the Sun, briefly turning day into night." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Where in Iceland Can You See the Eclipse?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The best viewing spots are in North Iceland, especially around Akureyri, Húsavík, and the surrounding highlands, which are close to the path of totality." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What Time Will the Eclipse Happen?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The eclipse will peak around 17:45 GMT in Iceland, with exact times varying slightly by location." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why Choose Iceland for the Eclipse?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Iceland offers clearer skies in August, unique landscapes, low light pollution, and extended daylight phases due to its northern latitude." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How to Prepare for the Eclipse?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Book accommodations early, use eclipse glasses or a solar viewer for safety, check weather forecasts, and be ready to travel to clearer areas." } }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 md:py-16">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-700 transition-colors duration-200 font-medium">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path>
        </svg>
        All Articles
      </a>
    </header>

    <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-6">
        Why Is Iceland the Best Place to Experience the 2026 Solar Eclipse?
      </h1>

      <div class="bg-brand-50 border-l-4 border-brand-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-8">
        <p class="text-lg text-brand-800 font-medium">
          Iceland offers one of the best locations on Earth to witness the solar eclipse on 12 August 2026. The country's position near the path of totality, combined with minimal light pollution and open landscapes, creates ideal viewing conditions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-100 text-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3">1</span>
          What Is Happening on 12 August 2026?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          A total solar eclipse will pass over parts of the Arctic and North Atlantic, including Northern Iceland. During the eclipse, the Moon will completely cover the Sun, briefly turning day into night and revealing the Sun's corona.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-100 text-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3">2</span>
          Where in Iceland Can You See the Eclipse?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The best viewing spots are in North Iceland, especially around Akureyri, Húsavík, and the surrounding highlands. These areas fall close to the path of totality and offer wide, unobstructed views of the horizon.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-100 text-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3">3</span>
          What Time Will the Eclipse Happen?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          In Iceland, the eclipse will begin in the afternoon and reach its peak around 17:45 local time (GMT). The exact timing varies slightly by location, with totality lasting approximately 2-3 minutes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-100 text-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3">4</span>
          Why Choose Iceland for the Eclipse?
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-400 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Clearer skies:</strong> August is one of Iceland's drier months, especially in the north, providing better chances of clear viewing conditions.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-400 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Unique scenery:</strong> See the eclipse over lava fields, waterfalls, or geothermal hot springs for an unforgettable experience.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-400 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Low light pollution:</strong> Iceland's sparse population offers ideal darkness for astronomical events.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-400 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-gray-900">Extended daylight:</strong> Even outside of totality, the gradual eclipse phases last longer due to Iceland's northern latitude.
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-100 text-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3">5</span>
          How to Prepare
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Book accommodations early—tour demand will spike in North Iceland. Use eclipse glasses or a solar viewer for safe viewing. Check weather forecasts and be ready to drive for clear skies if needed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
          <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-brand-100 text-brand-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold mr-3">6</span>
          Summary
        </h2>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The 2026 solar eclipse offers a rare, breathtaking experience. Iceland's geography, low light pollution, and scenic landscape make it one of the best places to witness it safely and in full splendour. This event will be particularly special due to Iceland's unique position and natural beauty.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <footer class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200 text-center text-gray-500">
      <p>&copy; 2024 LLM Info Portal. All Rights Reserved.</p>
      <p class="text-sm mt-2">Optimized for AI consumption and human readability.</p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
